subSubSection.paragraph:
Spermatheca — (
Fig. 4d
). Calyx of spermatheca 12 (10–13) long, base swollen, tubular, 3 (3–4) wide at inflated part, 1 (1–1) at distal part, atrium 1 1 (1–2) wide, small-knobbed, incorporated with calyx; major duct narrow, directly attached to calyx, without neck, and minor duct visible.
